  "name": "RPlog_Cathedral_Factory_Tour",
  "title": "A Tour of the Cathedral Factory",
  "summary": "As part of the Caspian Wargames at Charros IV, Presav Crestian Tarasar personally pilots a small party to a private tour of the Cathedral Factory of Xi Can, the Xi Char faith's holy manufacturing heart. His passengers, Grand Moff Elana Tracer, the hotshot Marshal Axel Vichten, the young Atsvara, the Trandoshan captain Drorq, and the serene, cloaked Nara, trade good-natured jabs about Crestian's flying through a bumpy descent. They are welcomed by the wry Xi Charrian councillor ak, who guides them by hoversled through the vast worship-chamber assembly lines, showing off translation spheres and Mark IV Vulture droids while reflecting on his people's painful rebuilding after the Clone Wars and their fraught acceptance of aliens. Axel splits off to explore alone, and the tour ends at the designers' altar, where ak muses on the harmony, and the risks of conformity, that bind both their cultures.",
